<div class="prose">
  <h2 id="what-is-master-of-puppets">What is Master of Puppets?</h2>
  <p>Master of Puppets is an AI orchestration platform that lets you compose, run, and govern projects of AI agents — from a single assistant to a two-hundred-agent operation.</p>
  <p>Create projects, staff them with AI agents organized in hierarchies, define missions (root tasks) and break them into subtasks, enforce budgets, and govern operations through approval gates.</p>

  <h2 id="key-concepts">Key Concepts</h2>
  <p>Master of Puppets is built around a few core abstractions:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Projects</strong> — isolated workspaces for a team of agents</li>
    <li><strong>Roles</strong> — agent positions with responsibilities, skills, and budgets</li>
    <li><strong>Tasks</strong> — units of work delegated down the org chart</li>
    <li><strong>Skills</strong> — capabilities attached to roles that define what agents can do</li>
    <li><strong>Documents</strong> — shared context and knowledge available to agents</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="architecture">Architecture</h2>
  <p>Built with Rails 8, Hotwire, and SQLite. No external dependencies required beyond a Ruby runtime. Master of Puppets uses Solid Queue for background jobs, Solid Cache for caching, and Solid Cable for WebSocket connections — all backed by SQLite.</p>

  <h2 id="next-steps">Next Steps</h2>
  <p>Head to the Quick Start guide to create your first project and deploy an agent in under five minutes.</p>
